text: IF  THEN Evaluate situations objectively, even when outcomes are ambiguous.
IF  THEN Seek environments and social groups that reinforce desired default behaviors.
IF  THEN Implement consistent routines to counteract negative default patterns.
IF  THEN Hold yourself accountable for your actions without relying on external validation.
IF  THEN Expect more from yourself than from others to drive personal improvement.
IF  THEN Take ownership of responsibilities to avoid excuses.
IF  THEN Be proactive in tasks, even small ones, to achieve better outcomes.
IF  THEN Evaluate actions for their impact on future outcomes
IF  THEN Take personal responsibility for results regardless of circumstances
IF  THEN Stick to areas of known expertise to avoid failure
IF  THEN Define clear boundaries for your knowledge and adhere to them
IF  THEN Actively develop self-control and strengths to mitigate acquired weaknesses and blind spots.
IF  THEN Implement regular self-assessment and perspective-taking to identify and address cognitive biases.
IF  THEN Decision-making should consider biological vulnerabilities (hunger, fatigue, etc.)
IF  THEN Never agree to requests immediately via phone
IF  THEN Only make decisions that support long-term goals
IF  THEN Establish clear, automatic behavioral rules to minimize friction
